summary:
Immediately after graduating I started volunteering as a physiotherapist in Samoa. This new view of the world has given me a different frame of reference within which care is provided and the great cultural differences have enriched my experience.

My specializations in the field of Dry Needling Myofascial Triggerpoints, Manual Myofascial Release Triggerpoint Therapy, Medical Taping Concept, Motivational Interviewing, Mulligan Manual Therapy Concept & Shockwave Therapy ensure that as a physiotherapist I can offer my patients the widest Evidence Based Practice treatment plan. I keep knowledge and skills up-to-date by following refresher courses and updating professional literature.
By communicating and giving the patient the opportunity to explain his complaints extensively and by asking specific questions, I arrive at a treatment plan.
I approach each patient respectfully and understand every complaint. By clinically reasoning and applying different interventions I achieve an optimal treatment result.

What started as a challenge to run the authentic marathon in Greece has now grown into a serious sport for me. Every year I participate in various marathons with the aim to finish within 4 hours. From my professional knowledge I work on (running) technique and I share my experiences, among others with my patients who also run.
The end is not yet in sight...
